column10:
It has both the morgan and the shinden, and you can do flips with PSM-capable jets.


if you managed to buy this before christmas,

<<here comes the snow>>

Fun gameplay in principle, but awful, horrendous mission design. The only fighter jet game, ever, where the missions are easier the slower(!) you can make your plane go. Flabbergasting.

Also:
* Random timers;
* Faceless uninspired drones as the main opponents;
* Grinding the same linear missions to unlock equipment that makes the missions less painful;
* Slowly spoken cut scenes that are incredibly tedious and have the worst writing; 
* No text-based mission briefings, which forces you to endure their awful, drawn-out writing in order to know what you're supposed to do.

Was looking forward to my first Ace Combat game, and was hoping it would get better after the first couple of awful missions, but it does not. Would return it, if I still could.

Ace-combat is an amazing game and is a very fun experience; dog-fighting feels tactile and immersive, the story is both cohesive and intriguing; however, the story mode which is the primary gameplay, while good, does not reflect a $85 AUD price tag; along side the fact that the DLC is far too expensive to be worthwhile.

If your filthy rich purchase it;
If your a die hard fan - purchase it;
If your not here for the story mode alone - purchase it;
But if you are primarily focused on story mode alone it's not worth the money.
